docs.abstract: The longest-serving Arab ruler, Qaboos pulled his nation from poverty and brokered quiet talks between global foes.
docs.snippet: The longest-serving Arab ruler, Qaboos pulled his nation from poverty and brokered quiet talks between global foes.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIRUT, Lebanon — Sultan Qaboos bin Said of Oman, who over nearly five decades in power transformed his Persian Gulf kingdom from an isolated enclave into a developed nation known for brokering quiet talks between global foes, has died, the Omani government announced on Saturday. He was 79.

headline.main: Sultan Qaboos, 79, Is Dead; Built Oman Into Prosperous Oasis of Peacemaking
headline.print_headline: Sultan Qaboos Dies at 79; Built Oman Into Prosperous Oasis of Peacemaking

docs.abstract: Richard Silvestri sets us off on a new year with a highly challenging cryptic crossword.
docs.snippet: Richard Silvestri sets us off on a new year with a highly challenging cryptic crossword.
docs.lead_paragraph: CRYPTIC CROSSWORD — Perhaps this will be the year variety puzzles go viral — they’re due, and the puzzlesphere is expanding. Maybe there will be a 100th monkey effect at some point. In hopes of that, I’m going to keep going over these puzzles clue by clue so that anyone who’s interested and humble enough to just give themselves over to this process will be able to finish each puzzle. If that’s you, I’m glad you’re here. By the end of the year, you’ll know what you’re doing at least as well as I do, and your brain will be all the more flexible and powerful for it.

docs.abstract: Wolf Cukier, 17, was analyzing brightness of stars during an internship with NASA last year when he made the discovery.
docs.snippet: Wolf Cukier, 17, was analyzing brightness of stars during an internship with NASA last year when he made the discovery.
docs.lead_paragraph: The summer before senior year of high school can be a stressful time for a teenager. Childhood is winding down. College applications loom large. Many students are looking for an edge that will help them get into the right school. Last year, Wolf Cukier, 17, spent his summer vacation as few other rising seniors have: He helped discover a planet.

headline.main: How’s Your Internship Going? This Teen Found a Planet
headline.print_headline: College Application Bonus: I Helped Discover a Planet

docs.abstract: Facebook, Google and other major tech firms were every student’s dream workplaces. Until they weren’t.
docs.snippet: Facebook, Google and other major tech firms were every student’s dream workplaces. Until they weren’t.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2006, Google bought YouTube for more than $1 billion, Apple was preparing to announce the first iPhone, and the American housing bubble began to deflate. Claire Stapleton, then a senior at the University of Pennsylvania, faced the same question over and over: What did she plan to do with that English degree? She flirted, noncommittally, with Teach for America.
